title: Test
summary: This grouped bar chart has 3 categories of Sex on the x axis representing 4 groups: All races / ethnicities, White (non-Hispanic), Black (non-Hispanic), and Hispanic.
Averaging these 4 groups, the highest category is found for Sex Male with a mean value of 7.12.
The lowest category is observed at Female that has a mean value of 4.78
showing a difference of 39.5% with the maximum value.

In case of Male, All races / ethnicities shows more dominance than any other Sex with a value 76.0 and it has the lowest value 55.0 in Female.  However, White (non-Hispanic) is the second impactful group, and it has the highest value 48.0 for Sex Male and the lowest 14.0 in case of Female.
